Malawi will impose a 15 pct "border tax" onsome overseas remittances and a five pct profit tax for localbranches of foreign firms to boost revenue and meet a projected1987/88 budget deficit of 303 mln kwacha, the Malawi newsagency reported.    Finance Minister Dalton Katopola, presenting the newbudget, said other measures would include raising surtax ongoods and services by five points to 35 pct and imposing dutyon luxury goods and tax on statutory bodies such as the WaterBoard.    Malawi's economy was expected to grow 2.3 pct this year, hesaid. REUTER&#3;